cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on distributed edge computing, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless edge networks and communication scheduling, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the optimal computation-communication co-design, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper characterizes the optimal computation allocation policy and scheduling order of communications, which are related to information theory. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the optimal selection of devices, which can be related to multiagent systems.
